| Parameter knowledge | Built-in schema | Requires `full` detail | **Extra call or guessing** |
| Server visibility | 9/9 | 3/9 | **-67%** |
| Caching within conversation | N/A | ‚úÖ 60min TTL | Works |
| Search by server name | N/A | ‚úÖ Works | Good |
| Cross-server queries | N/A | ‚úÖ Works | Good |

---

## 11. Alternative Architecture Ideas

### Option A: Stable Keys + Optional Discovery
```
# Direct call if you know the tool
tool_execute(key="slack:channels_list", args={})

# Discovery still available for exploration
tool_discovery(query=["slack"]) ‚Üí returns stable keys
```

### Option B: Pre-registered Tool Shortcuts
```
# Common tools have shorthand
tool_execute(shortcut="calendar", args={...}) ‚Üí routes to get_events
tool_execute(shortcut="unread_texts", args={}) ‚Üí routes to imessage:get_unread
```

### Option C: Capability-Based Auto-Routing
```
# Describe what you want, router picks the tool
tool_request(
  intent="get calendar events",
  context={"timeframe": "this week", "account": "rob@loop.co"}
) ‚Üí auto-discovers and executes get_events
```

